'''Maximilian Beier''' ({{IPA|de|maksɪˈmiːli̯an ˈbaɪ̯ɐ|-|}}; born 17 October 2002) is a German professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] or [[Winger (association football)|winger]] for [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia Dortmund]] and the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]].

==Club career==
===2020–21: Professional debut===
Beier started playing football for [[Brandenburger SC Süd 05|Brandenburger SC Süd]], then moved to [[Energie Cottbus]], almost quitting football because of homesickness.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Maximilian Beier |url=https://www.bvb.de/de/en/teams/football/player/maximilian-beier.html |access-date=2025-08-13 |website=www.bvb.de}}</ref> Beier moved to [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]] at the age of 15,<ref>{{Cite web |title=Borussia Dortmund's Maximilian Beier on his "crazy" rise to the top |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/maximilian-beier-interview-borussia-dortmund-germany-crazy-rise-hoffenheim-28805 |access-date=2025-08-13 |website=www.bundesliga.com |language=en}}</ref> where he made his professional debut in the [[Bundesliga]] in a 1–0 defeat against [[SC Freiburg|Freiburg]] on 8 February 2020, coming on in the 88th minute for [[Robert Skov]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ca.soccerway.com/matches/2020/02/08/germany/bundesliga/sc-freiburg/tsg-1899-hoffenheim-ev/3047207/|title=Freiburg 1–0 Hoffenheim|publisher=Soccerway|date=8 February 2020}}</ref> Later that year, on 10 December, he recorded his first goals by scoring twice and providing an assist in a 4–1 win against [[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]] in the [[2020–21 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.tsg-hoffenheim.de/en/news/overview/2020/12/tsg-round-off-group-with-comfortable-win-over-gent/ |title=TSG round off group with comfortable win over Gent |publisher=TSG Hoffenheim |date=10 December 2020 }}</ref>

===2021–2023: Loan to Hannover 96===
On 19 August 2021, Beier was loaned out to [[Hannover 96]] for one season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/auf-leihbasis-hannover-eist-beier-von-hoffenheim-los-868806/artikel |title=Auf Leihbasis: Hannover eist Beier von Hoffenheim los |website=[[Kicker (magazine)|Kicker]] |publisher=[[Kicker (sports magazine)|kicker]] |date=19 August 2021 |access-date=19 August 2021 |language=de}}</ref> The loan was extended for the 2022–23 season on 8 June 2022.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Hannover 96|url=https://www.hannover96.de/aktuelles/news/details/30615-beier-bleibt-leihe-aus-hoffenheim-wird-verlaengert.html|title=Leihe aus Hoffenheim wird verlängert|date=8 June 2022|access-date=22 July 2022|language=de}}</ref>

===2023–24: Return to Hoffenheim and breakthrough===
He returned to Hoffenheim for the [[2023–24 Bundesliga|2023–24 season]], and became the club's top scorer, netting 16 goals across 33 games.<ref>{{Cite web|last=Sharma|first=Abhinav|url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/bundesliga-top-scorers-2023-24/blt5cb7bb94f705632b#cs3f7f617234dfcb59|title=Bundesliga top scorers 2023-24: Harry Kane, Serhou Guirassy & players with the most goals in Germany this season|publisher=Goal.com|date=19 May 2024}}</ref>

===Borussia Dortmund (since 2024)===
On 12 August 2024, Beier joined fellow Bundesliga side [[Borussia Dortmund]], signing a five-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bvb.de/de/en/news/news-overview/news.html/2024/8/12/BVB-sign-Maximilian-Beier.html|title=BVB sign Maximilian Beier|publisher=Borussia Dortmund|date=12 August 2024|access-date=12 August 2024}}</ref> Beier made his debut in the [[2024–25 DFB-Pokal|DFB Pokal]] on 17 August 2024.<ref>{{Cite web |author=CIARÁN FAHEY|agency=Associated Press |date=2024-08-17 |title=Positivo debut con Sahin con el Dortmund gana en su presentación en la Copa Alemana |url=https://www.latimes.com/espanol/deportes/articulo/2024-08-17/positivo-debut-con-sahin-con-el-dortmund-gana-4-1-en-su-presentacion-en-la-copa-alemana |access-date=2024-08-18 |website=Los Angeles Times en Español |language=en}}</ref> On 12 March 2025, Beier scored his first [[UEFA Champions League]] goal in the second leg of the Round of 16 matchup against [[Lille OSC|Lille]] to push the aggregate to 3–2 and propel Dortmund into the quarterfinals of the [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League]] campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reuters.com/sports/soccer/dortmund-beat-lille-reach-champions-league-quarters-again-2025-03-12/|title=Second-half comeback sends Dortmund into Champions League quarters again|website=[[Reuters]]|date=March 12, 2025|access-date=March 12, 2025}}</ref> He ended his first season at Dortmund with ten goals scored across the [[2024–25 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]], Champions League and [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup|Club World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Maximilian Beier {{!}} Statistiken {{!}} Bundesliga 2025/26 |url=https://www.kicker.de/maximilian-beier/spieler-spieldaten |access-date=2026-03-26 |website=kicker |language=de-DE}}</ref> In the [[2025–26 Bundesliga|following season]], he'd help side finish runner-up in the league, registering ten goals and assists each in all competitions, earning a call-up to the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Maximilian Beier {{!}} Borussia Dortmund {{!}} Bundesliga {{!}} 2025/26 {{!}} Spielerprofil |url=https://www.kicker.de/maximilian-beier/spieler |access-date=2026-05-20 |website=kicker |language=de-DE}}</ref>

==International career==
Beier was a youth international footballer for Germany.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://datencenter.dfb.de/datencenter/personen/maximilian-beier/spieler|title=Maximilian Beier Personenprofil|publisher=[[German Football Association]]|language=de}}</ref> In March 2024, he was called up for the [[Germany national football team|Germany national team]] ahead of the friendly matches against [[France national football team|France]] and the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dfb.de/news/detail/start-ins-em-jahr-mit-sechs-neulingen-und-sechs-rueckkehrern-259584/|title=Start ins EM-Jahr mit sechs Neulingen und sechs Rückkehrern|date=14 March 2024|publisher=German Football Association|access-date=14 March 2024|language=de }}</ref>

He was named in Germany's squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2024]].<ref>{{cite web |date=7 June 2024 |title=UEFA Euro 2024: All squads and players full list |url=https://olympics.com/en/news/uefa-euro-2024-all-squads-and-players-full-list |access-date=7 June 2024 |website=Olympics.com}}</ref> On 3 June, he made his senior debut in a friendly match against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]] prior to the tournament.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rnd.de/sport/deutschland-ukraine-die-einzelkritik-der-dfb-elf-im-ueberblick-FSJBWFPFJJBV7GLCQ7K2REIUX4.html |title=Kein Tor gegen die Ukraine: Vier Zweien, aber auch eine Fünf für DFB-Stars |publisher=RND |language=de |date=3 June 2024 }}</ref> Beier made one appearance across the tournament, playing 26 minutes after replacing [[Robert Andrich]] in a 1–1 draw against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=Switzerland vs Germany {{!}} Timeline {{!}} UEFA EURO 2024 |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036185--switzerland-vs-germany/timeline/ |access-date=2025-08-13 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref> Germany was knocked out by [[Spain national football team|Spain]] in the quarter-finals.<ref>{{Cite web |last=UEFA.com |title=Spain vs Germany {{!}} UEFA EURO 2024 |url=https://www.uefa.com/euro2024/match/2036205--spain-vs-germany/ |access-date=2025-08-13 |website=UEFA.com |language=en}}</ref> On 21 May 2026, he'd be called up to Germany's final squad ahead of the [[2026 FIFA World Cup|FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Beier wohl ebenfalls in Nagelsmanns WM-Aufgebot |url=https://www.kicker.de/beier-wohl-ebenfalls-in-nagelsmanns-wm-aufgebot-1221373/artikel |access-date=2026-05-20 |website=kicker |language=de-DE}}</ref>

